<br>
1) Sneaky type. Stealth skills, backstab, poisons, climbing. Poor Melee<br>
<br>
2) Archer type. Some steath, archery, reasonable melee.<br>
<br>
General consensus is as you say, they are among the weaker PvE classes, having to rely on groups much more than others.<br>
<br>
However, when it comes to RvR, they rock da house.<br>
<br>
RvR is a large part of DaoC. Basically the whole 30+ game is centered around it.<br>
<br>
So, if you want to kick ass in RvR, then sure play one of those classes, however, be very aware that you will have a lot of frustration at lower levels, struggling to solo blue cons, and dying a lot unless you group, while others around you are soloing yellows and kicking ass.<br>
<br>
