<br>
I have no trouble soloing blues, but apparently I am in the minority.  I can solo blues for a whole level and never die.  Maybe its having mostly yellow armor and yellow/orange weapons.  Maybe its my skill point distribution (lots of Stealth/CritStrike, some Envenom), or maybe it's the way I play.  Anyway, your milage may vary, and I would never even try a yellow - no chance.<br>
<br>
However, Sanya has stated that they plan to beef up rogues PvE skills so that we can kill blues without our specials and kill yellows with our specials.  Right now, its one step down - we can kill blues with our specials working perfectly, and greens without our specials.  She said that rogues have been doing well in RvR, so while they will tweak us a little in that respect (poisons haven't been working properly), they have no major plans for the high level rogues.<br>
<br>
I think its a very fun class.  If you like sneaking around, thinking hard, waiting 30 seconds to set up a Backstab to start a fight (that's in PvE, sometimes 10 minutes in RvR) then this is an awesome class.  Definitely the hardest to play in both PvE and RvR, since you have to get very close to your target to attack, and once you attack you are going to die very quickly if anyone else sees you, or the person you attack is stronger than you thought, or you miss your opening attack.<br>
<br>
If you like constant action, running up and whacking things and knowing you can tank them, then you will hate this class like no other.  Rogues in Camelot are NOT damage dealers like in EQ - the stealth is our defining feature. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=144.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showNextMessage?topicID=144.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.emailToFriend?topicID=144.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.threadControl?topicID=144.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=144.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=144.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="monklybusiness43508